---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Privacy · Ekbatan"
    description="Privacy policy for the Ekbatan framework website, documentation, examples, agent skills, and Claude Code plugin."
>
    <section class="border-b-2 border-ink">
        <div class="container-px max-w-4xl mx-auto py-20 md:py-28">
            <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 brutalist-border bg-ink text-paper font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest px-3 py-1.5">
                <span class="text-yellow">§</span><span>Privacy</span>
            </div>

            <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-5xl md:text-7xl tracking-tight text-balance mt-6 leading-[0.95]">
                Privacy policy
            </h1>

            <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed">
                This page describes how the Ekbatan framework website,
                documentation, examples, agent skills, and Claude Code plugin
                handle data.
            </p>

            <div class="mt-12 brutalist-border bg-paper p-6 md:p-8 space-y-8 text-base leading-relaxed">
                <section>
                    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
                        Summary
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-3">
                        Ekbatan is an open-source Java persistence/action
                        framework. The public website, documentation, examples,
                        agent skills, and Claude Code plugin are developer
                        resources for learning and working with that framework.
                        Ekbatan does not operate a hosted application service,
                        hosted API, or user account system.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
                        Data collection
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-3">
                        The Ekbatan framework, website, documentation, examples,
                        agent skills, and Claude Code plugin do not
                        intentionally collect personal information. They do not
                        collect telemetry, create user accounts, store personal
                        data, or send data to Zyraz/Ekbatan servers.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
                        Claude and agent sessions
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-3">
                        When you use the Ekbatan Claude Code plugin, your
                        prompts, source files, tool calls, and command output
                        are handled by your Claude Code session and by
                        Anthropic according to Anthropic's terms and privacy
                        policies. Ekbatan does not receive a copy of those
                        sessions.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
                        Local files and commands
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-3">
                        Some skills may instruct an AI coding agent to read
                        local project files or run local verification commands.
                        Those actions happen in your development environment
                        and are controlled by your agent's permission settings.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
                        Third-party services
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-3">
                        If you use Claude, GitHub, Maven Central, package
                        registries, CI systems, or other third-party services
                        while working with Ekbatan, those services process data
                        under their own policies.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
                        Contact
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mt-3">
                        For privacy questions about Ekbatan, open an issue in
                        the public repository at
                        <a
                            href="https://github.com/zyraz-io/ekbatan/issues"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noreferrer"
                            class="font-mono underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:bg-yellow"
                            >github.com/zyraz-io/ekbatan/issues</a
                        >.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-ink/60 border-t-2 border-ink pt-4">
                    Last updated: June 20, 2026
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
